number="2",
pages="125--133",
abstract="Experimenting with large-scale, multi-agent software systems yields insight into factors that determine the capability of complex systems to operate at the edge of chaos without disintegrating. The research results are generalised and applied to the diagnosis of the failure of the global financial system.",
